This paper examines the impact of social networks on suicide ideation, which falls under the category of social influence and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper analyzes a large dataset obtained from a social networking service, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). The paper also discusses the logistic regression model, which falls under the category of computational methods, making cs.CR (Computational Complexity) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of social isolation on suicide ideation, which could also fall under the category of human-computer interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a possible sub-category.
